        Places to avoid... okay, not AVOID exactly, but be careful? — The territories outside the facility all have different customs and different... temperaments. Some of them are super friendly to visitors and some of them are more "why are you in my forest, soft creature?" — So just... don't wander off without your guide. I learned this the hard way. — I mean, I crashed here, so I didn't exactly have a choice about my entrance - long story, spaceship malfunction, very dramatic — but even after that, I definitely got lost a few times before I figured out how things worked.

        Oh! How are you planning to get here, by the way? — That's actually a genuine question because my arrival method was, uh, not recommended.

        ¶

        Anyway. — I'm so excited for you! — Write me when you get here. — Or before. — Or during. — Just write me, honestly, I want to hear how it goes. — And if you end up at the facility, ask for me! — I'll show you around. — We can compare notes on Captain Vex's diplomatic disasters.

        Safe travels, fellow adventurer! —

        - Kira

        P.S. - If anyone offers you something to eat that's still visibly photosynthesizing, it's polite to try a bite, but you don't have to finish it. — Trust me on this one.
